-- Dai-Ichi Life to buy Protective Life for $5.7 bln - filing
-- By Emi Emoto and Taiga Uranaka
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 08:38PM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, June 4 (Reuters) - Dai-Ichi Life Insurance Co <8750.T> will buy U.S. peer Protective Life <PL.N> for $5.708 billion (582.2 billion yen), funding part of that by issuing up to 250 billion yen ($2.4 billion) in new shares, according to a regulatory filing made on Wednesday.

